1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
What if I told you your cells have a ticking clock?

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:09,200
Meet telomeres — the protective caps at the ends of your chromosomes.

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:14,000
Every time a cell divides, these caps wear down, shortening your lifespan.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:19,600
Telomerase is an enzyme that can rebuild these caps, but it’s not a cure-all.

5
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:24,000
Understanding telomeres gives us a glimpse into the biology of aging.

6
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,400
Curious about how this affects you?

7
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,800
Like and follow for more insights!
